This is true by the definition of `support` and `dart`.
A dart `(a,b)` means there's an edge from `a` to `b`. The support is the list of vertices visited.
If `(w, w_1)` is a dart, then `w_1` is the next vertex after `w` in the walk. So `w_1` must be in the support set.
The chosen tactics (`simp`, `try { tauto }`, etc.) are not robust enough to establish this.

